She was the most beautiful thing
I'd ever seen.

733
01:26:02,891 --> 01:26:05,189
And I was shy then.

734
01:26:05,326 --> 01:26:08,557
So when she would look at me,

735
01:26:08,696 --> 01:26:10,687
I would look away.

736
01:26:12,267 --> 01:26:15,168
Then, afterwards,
when I would look back,

737
01:26:15,303 --> 01:26:17,498
she would look away.

738
01:26:19,007 --> 01:26:25,173
Then I got to where I was gonna get
off, and got off. The doors closed.

739
01:26:27,081 --> 01:26:32,644
And as the train was pulling away,
she looked right at me

740
01:26:32,787 --> 01:26:35,483
and gave me the most incredible smile.

741
01:26:38,593 --> 01:26:42,689
It was awful.
I wanted to tear the doors open.

742
01:26:42,830 --> 01:26:47,767
I went back every night,
same time, for two weeks.

743
01:26:50,838 --> 01:26:53,534
But she never showed up.

744
01:26:55,376 --> 01:26:57,640
That was 30 years ago.

745
01:26:58,846 --> 01:27:03,613
And I don't think there's a day
that goes by that I don't think about her.

746
01:27:05,620 --> 01:27:08,748
I don't want that to happen again.

747
01:27:15,129 --> 01:27:16,824
Just one dance?

748
01:30:48,209 --> 01:30:50,541
You wanted the driver's side...

749
01:30:51,479 --> 01:30:53,709
I want a word with you, Gage.

750
01:30:53,848 --> 01:30:57,750
What you don't know is
we got a secret, me and Diana.

751
01:30:57,885 --> 01:30:59,284
We're invincible.

752
01:31:00,822 --> 01:31:04,451
- Diana, I need to talk...
- Tomorrow might be a better time.

753
01:31:04,592 --> 01:31:06,822
Tomorrow might be better, you think?

754
01:31:06,961 --> 01:31:08,986
Johnny-baby,
I got a suggestion for you.

755
01:31:09,130 --> 01:31:14,193
You know that emblem you got?
The gryphon? The eagle?

756
01:31:14,335 --> 01:31:18,396
I don't think it's a good idea.
I got a better idea.

757
01:31:18,539 --> 01:31:23,670
How about the cuckoo? Because...
I'm talking to you for a second.

758
01:31:23,811 --> 01:31:26,974
The cuckoo is interesting.
It doesn't have its own nest,

759
01:31:27,114 --> 01:31:30,880
so it moves into the nest of other birds
and destroys their eggs.

760
01:31:31,018 --> 01:31:32,542
David, stop.

761
01:31:35,890 --> 01:31:38,051
You don't love me any more?

762
01:31:43,264 --> 01:31:46,358
Have I ever told you I love you?

763
01:31:50,571 --> 01:31:53,096
Have a nice dinner.

764
01:31:54,909 --> 01:31:56,934
- Help him.
- Here.

765
01:31:58,446 --> 01:32:00,073
Go inside.

766
01:32:00,214 --> 01:32:03,012
You got him?

767
01:32:05,019 --> 01:32:07,283
D.

768
01:34:33,601 --> 01:34:37,093
You've done a lot since USC.

769
01:34:37,238 --> 01:34:41,265
First in your class. AIA award.

770
01:34:41,409 --> 01:34:44,867
- Prix de Rome.
- Yeah.

771
01:34:46,313 --> 01:34:49,146
Why would you want this job?

772
01:34:49,283 --> 01:34:52,343
Well, I wanna work.

773
01:34:55,990 --> 01:34:57,787
Overqualified.

774
01:34:58,359 --> 01:35:00,850
Fine. Exploit me.

775
01:35:36,897 --> 01:35:39,593
Great architecture
only comes from your passion,

776
01:35:39,734 --> 01:35:41,998
and even that won't assure you a job.

777
01:35:42,136 --> 01:35:44,696
Louis Kahn.

778
01:35:44,839 --> 01:35:49,003
Died in a men's room in Penn Station.
For days, no one claimed the body.

779
01:35:49,143 --> 01:35:50,940
Look at that. Is that beautiful?

780
01:35:51,078 --> 01:35:53,273
The money men did not weep,

781
01:35:53,414 --> 01:35:56,144
because the great ones
are impossible to deal with.

782
01:35:56,283 --> 01:36:01,380
They're a pain in the ass, because they
know that if they do their jobs properly,

783
01:36:01,522 --> 01:36:03,888
if they just this once get it right,

784
01:36:04,024 --> 01:36:08,552
they can actually lift the human spirit,
take it to a higher place.

785
01:36:13,968 --> 01:36:16,528
- What is this?
- A brick.

786
01:36:18,038 --> 01:36:20,370
Good. What else?

787
01:36:20,508 --> 01:36:22,442
A weapon.

788
01:36:25,679 --> 01:36:30,048
Louis Kahn said, "Even a brick
wants to be something."

789
01:36:36,924 --> 01:36:40,917
A brick wants to be something.

790
01:36:43,164 --> 01:36:45,132
It aspires.

791
01:36:51,405 --> 01:36:56,741
Even a common, ordinary brick
wants to be something more than it is.

792
01:37:01,949 --> 01:37:05,783
Wants to be something better than it is.

793
01:37:13,627 --> 01:37:15,754
That is what we must be.

794
01:37:19,600 --> 01:37:21,932
See you on Friday.

795
01:37:32,980 --> 01:37:36,711
A brick wants to be something?
I bet it doesn't want to be a lawyer.

796
01:37:36,851 --> 01:37:39,285
- What are you doing here?
- I missed you.

797
01:37:39,920 --> 01:37:43,083
- I missed you, too.
- Thanks.

798
01:37:47,995 --> 01:37:50,520
- How you doin'?
- I'm good.

799
01:37:50,664 --> 01:37:52,689
I'm getting it together.

800
01:37:58,138 --> 01:38:00,129
She wants a divorce.

801
01:38:03,110 --> 01:38:05,374
She wants her freedom.

802
01:38:06,914 --> 01:38:10,611
If you don't contest it,
you get everything.

803
01:38:10,751 --> 01:38:14,187
The land, the money. Everything.

804
01:38:15,189 --> 01:38:17,054
Where is she?

805
01:38:25,766 --> 01:38:29,099
Hi, everybody. I'm Billy Connolly.
Goodbye, everybody.

806
01:38:29,236 --> 01:38:33,002
You may wonder what you're doing
here, sitting in the blazing sun,

807
01:38:33,140 --> 01:38:36,769
as the smell of the zoo
wafts past your nostrils.

808
01:38:36,911 --> 01:38:40,642
The reason you are here
is because you are loaded.

809
01:38:40,781 --> 01:38:43,375
May I say how brilliant it is
to see so many people

810
01:38:43,517 --> 01:38:46,714
with an interest in the preservation
of endangered species.

811
01:38:46,854 --> 01:38:50,221
Every year, we have this unique way
of making money for the cause.

812
01:38:50,357 --> 01:38:53,918
We auction animals.
We bid as high as we possibly can,

813
01:38:54,061 --> 01:38:56,621
and the money goes
to sponsor these lovely beasts.

814
01:38:56,764 --> 01:39:01,167
Let's start the show with a bang. We've
got a superstar as our first animal.

815
01:39:01,302 --> 01:39:04,601
Ladies and gentlemen, the hippo.

816
01:39:04,738 --> 01:39:08,504
The animal itself
is far too big and angry to bring along.

817
01:39:08,642 --> 01:39:12,237
Look at this guy.
Thousands and thousands of pounds

818
01:39:12,379 --> 01:39:15,314
of aggressive, hostile cellulite.

819
01:39:15,449 --> 01:39:18,384
Weighs slightly less
than the average school bus.

820
01:39:18,519 --> 01:39:21,181
And look at that magnificent beastie.

821
01:39:21,322 --> 01:39:26,350
To put him in a better light,
to relieve you of some serious money...

822
01:39:26,493 --> 01:39:28,688
Thank you very much.

823
01:39:28,829 --> 01:39:31,229
...we have a kissy-kissy picture.

824
01:39:32,366 --> 01:39:34,493
Isn't that nice?

825
01:39:37,204 --> 01:39:42,141
Ladies and gentlemen, I couldn't dream
of starting the bid below $10,000.

826
01:39:42,276 --> 01:39:44,608
- Now, I know it's a lot of money...
- 30.

827
01:39:44,745 --> 01:39:48,545
$30,000, ladies and gentlemen!

828
01:39:49,750 --> 01:39:54,346
Call me a sentimental old fool,
do I hear 35?

829
01:39:54,488 --> 01:39:57,355
- 35.
- $35,000!

830
01:39:57,491 --> 01:40:00,016
- 40.
- $40,000!

831
01:40:00,160 --> 01:40:02,390
45,000.

832
01:40:02,529 --> 01:40:05,896
- 50.
- $50,000.

833
01:40:06,967 --> 01:40:11,165
I can't believe it. That's extraordinary.
50,000 once,

834
01:40:11,305 --> 01:40:14,570
50,000 twice, ladies and gentlemen...

835
01:40:14,708 --> 01:40:17,404
One million dollars.

836
01:40:23,384 --> 01:40:24,783
I'm sorry?

837
01:40:24,918 --> 01:40:27,182
One million dollars.

838
01:40:29,690 --> 01:40:32,420
Did you say one million dollars, sir?

839
01:40:32,559 --> 01:40:34,151
Yeah.

840
01:40:34,294 --> 01:40:37,855
Ladies and gentlemen,
one million dollars.

841
01:40:39,266 --> 01:40:42,997
Would anybody care to top that,
ladies and gentlemen?

842
01:40:43,137 --> 01:40:44,399
I didn't think so.

843
01:40:44,538 --> 01:40:47,905
In that case, sir, I believe you're
the proud owner of a hippo.

844
01:40:48,042 --> 01:40:49,634
Congratulations.

845
01:41:03,624 --> 01:41:06,252
Hello, Diana.

846
01:41:06,393 --> 01:41:08,190
The next animal to take the stand
is an ostrich...

847
01:41:08,328 --> 01:41:10,455
I really wanted you to have that money.

848
01:41:10,597 --> 01:41:13,065
I really wanted you to have that hippo.

849
01:41:17,071 --> 01:41:20,302
Maybe you two would like
a moment alone.

850
01:41:33,987 --> 01:41:35,750
So...

851
01:41:38,725 --> 01:41:40,488
- How are you...
- I hear you're teaching...

852
01:41:40,627 --> 01:41:43,425
- Sorry.
- Go ahead.

853
01:41:43,564 --> 01:41:45,930
Yeah. I'm teaching.

854
01:41:48,302 --> 01:41:53,137
You know, it doesn't pay much, but
at least I get to talk about architecture.

855
01:41:53,273 --> 01:41:56,674
You know how I love
to talk about architecture.

856
01:41:58,412 --> 01:42:01,848
Don't leave, ladies and gentlemen.
It's just a shower.

857
01:42:01,982 --> 01:42:05,281
A cheque book
makes an ideal umbrella.

858
01:42:05,419 --> 01:42:08,547
Do we have a dolphin?
Have we a dolphin and an octopus?

859
01:42:08,689 --> 01:42:10,748
How about tropical fish?

860
01:42:10,891 --> 01:42:13,826
I know. You're running home
for more cash.

861
01:42:13,961 --> 01:42:17,522
Come on, ladies and gentlemen.
You can find the money.

862
01:42:17,664 --> 01:42:20,132
To hell. I'm gone.

863
01:42:29,443 --> 01:42:31,741
I have to talk to you
about what happened.

864
01:42:31,879 --> 01:42:34,507
- Don't.
- No. I have to.

865
01:42:34,648 --> 01:42:37,446
Just hear me out.

866
01:42:39,686 --> 01:42:42,917
I think the mistake I made in Vegas

867
01:42:43,056 --> 01:42:47,254
was thinking that I could
forget what we did.

868
01:42:48,595 --> 01:42:51,723
I thought we were invincible.

869
01:42:52,833 --> 01:42:58,772
Now I know that the things that people
in love do to each other, they remember.

870
01:42:58,906 --> 01:43:02,239
And if they stay together,
it's not because they forget,

871
01:43:02,376 --> 01:43:04,310
it's because they forgive.

872
01:43:11,285 --> 01:43:13,276
I was just...

873
01:43:16,223 --> 01:43:19,624
I was just so afraid
that you wanted him.

874
01:43:20,661 --> 01:43:23,824
No, actually, I was afraid
you were right to want him.

875
01:43:29,102 --> 01:43:32,538
I thought he was the better man.

876
01:43:37,611 --> 01:43:42,844
And I know now he's not.
He's just got more money.

877
01:45:15,475 --> 01:45:17,340
I think we should talk.

878
01:45:18,245 --> 01:45:20,236
I am very happy.

879
01:45:21,682 --> 01:45:25,482
Shackleford,
have you ever seen me like this?

880
01:45:26,820 --> 01:45:29,152
Can't say that I have.

881
01:45:29,289 --> 01:45:33,282
- Diana's the reason.
- Enough for any man.

882
01:45:33,427 --> 01:45:37,488
She is the best of them. Absolutely.

883
01:45:38,699 --> 01:45:40,496
You are the best of them.

884
01:45:42,002 --> 01:45:44,061
